Stray are a British band, formed in 1966. The vocalist 
Steve Gadd (born 27 April 1952, Shepherd's Bush, London) 
guitarist Del Bromham (born Derek Roy Bromham, 25 November 
1951, Acton, London), bass player Gary Giles (born Gary 
Stephen Giles, 23 February 1952, North Kensington, London) 
and drummer Steve Crutchley (born c 1952) formed the band
whilst all were attending the Christopher Wren School in 
London. Richard "Ritchie" Cole (born 10 November 1951, 
Shepherd's Bush, London) replaced Crutchley in 1968. They 
signed to Transatlantic Records in January 1970.
